link - http://ompl.kavrakilab.org/installation.html

sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://packages.ros.org/ros/ubuntu `lsb_release -sc` main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros-latest.list'
wget http://packages.ros.org/ros.key -O - | sudo apt-key add -

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install ros-indigo-ompl
################## apparenetly this alone works well #############

If the above doesnt work, do the following as well:

download the script file......
In the script file, make the changes:
line 25 g++-5 to g++-4.8 or which ever version in your laptop

./install-ompl-ubuntu.sh in the same directory as the install script.

DO NOT INSTALL WITH PYTHON BINDINGS 


